  + [dictated_source_ascii_transcription] is:
    "Zeta Oscilloscope, recommended definition, clean plus RH-relevant.
    Define the Zeta Oscilloscope, Lambda-Oscilloscope, by E_(t,N) using the von Mangoldt function Lambda(n), a damping parameter, t as the height/frequency parameter so s = sigma + it, and N as a finite computational cutoff.
    Visualization plots the moving point (Re(E_(t,N)), Im(E_(t,N))) as t varies.
    This produces a complex-plane waveform driven by prime-power oscillators, where each term Lambda(n) n^{-sigma} e^{-itn} acts as a rotating phasor with angular velocity n.
    At sigma = 1/2, the system is critically normalized, aligning the Oscilloscope with the analytic structure of the Riemann zeta function along Re(s)=1/2."
  + [known_tuning_fault] is source sketch uses e^{-i t n} and angular velocity n where zeta-aligned Dirichlet terms require e^{-i t log n} and angular velocity log(n)
  + [source_purpose] is to create a corrected .sop definition that preserves the visual instrument while aligning the phasor formula with zeta function structure

  = must: preserve this dictated source as the original-purpose anchor
  = must: correct the phase term in the canonical definition
  = must: preserve finite cutoff as part of the instrument
